<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 3061/91 of 18 October 1991 on the take-over by the intervention agencies of certain agricultural products intended for the people of the Soviet Union </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 3061/91 teatavate N&otilde;ukogude Liidu rahvale etten&auml;htud p&otilde;llumajandussaaduste ja -toodete &uuml;lev&otilde;tmise kohta sekkumisametite poolt 18. oktoober 1991 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 598/91 of 5 March 1981 on urgent action for the supply of agricultural products intended for the people of the Soviet Union (1), and in particular Article 5 (2) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 5. m&auml;rtsi 1981. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 598/91 kiireloomuliste meetmete kohta N&otilde;ukogude Liidu rahvale p&otilde;llumajandussaaduste ja -toodete tarnimiseks, (1) eriti selle artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1676/85 of 11 June 1985 on the value of the unit of account and the conversion rates to be applied for the purposes of the common agricultural policy (2), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2205/90 (3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 11. juuni 1985. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1676/85 &uuml;hise p&otilde;llumajanduspoliitika raames kohaldatava arvestus&uuml;hiku v&auml;&auml;rtuse ja konverteerimiskursside kohta, (2) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2205/90, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas by Regulation (EEC) No 598/91 the Council decided to supply free to the people of the Soviet Union agricultural products available from intervention or mobilized on the Community market in the case of specific needs; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: n&otilde;ukogu on m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 598/91 otsustanud tasuta tarnida N&otilde;ukogude Liidu rahvale sekkumises saadaolevaid v&otilde;i erivajaduste korral &uuml;henduse turult varutavaid p&otilde;llumajandussaaduseid ja -tooteid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for the purposes of applying this measure, invitations to tender were opened for the manufacture and packaging of the various products which are to be taken over with a view to their carriage to and distribution at the destination by the bodies selected by the Commission; whereas, in many cases, the latter bodies are not able to take over the products by the deadline laid down in the various invitations to tender for them to be made available; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealuse meetme kohaldamiseks on v&auml;lja kuulutatud pakkumismenetlused &uuml;lev&otilde;etavate toodete valmistamiseks ja pakendamiseks ning komisjoni poolt valitud asutuste poolt vedamiseks sihtkohta ja jaotamiseks sihtkohas; k&otilde;nealused asutused ei suuda paljudel juhtudel v&otilde;tta asjaomaseid tooteid &uuml;le t&auml;htajaks, mis on pakkumismenetluses toodete k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemiseks s&auml;testatud; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2946/91 of 7 October 1991 on the defraying of certain costs relating to food aid for the people of the Soviet Union (4) lays down the conditions under which the Community is to finance additional storage costs incurred by such late take-over by the bodies responsible for the carriage of the products to the destination; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni 7. oktoobri 1991. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;) nr 2946/91 teatavate N&otilde;ukogude Liidu rahvale antava toiduabiga seotud kulude katmise kohta (4) s&auml;testatakse tingimused, mille alusel &uuml;hendus finantseerib ladustamise lisakulud, mis tulenevad toodete hilisest &uuml;lev&otilde;tmisest toodete sihtkohta vedamise eest vastutava asutuse poolt; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, owing to the persistence of particular difficulties encountered in the carriage of this emergency aid, provision should be made for the requisite measures to cope with an extension of the period of storage before take-over by the bodies responsible for carriage; whereas, as far as possible, in order not to hinder in particular the carriage of the aid, those measures must consist in concluding contracts for storage in loco with the undertakings awarded contracts for the manufacture of the products, against payment of a daily allowance fixed taking into account the various costs arising from the extension of storage and the lodging of a suitable security; whereas, however, in the absence of agreement from those undertakings, provision should be made for the actual take-over of the products by the intervention agencies and storage under their responsibility; </inglise>
<eesti> otsetoetuse raames toimuval kauba veol esinevate eriliste raskuste p&uuml;simise t&otilde;ttu tuleks s&auml;testada asjakohased meetmed, millega n&auml;hakse ette pikendada veo eest vastutava asutuse poolsele toodete &uuml;lev&otilde;tmisele eelnevat ladustusaega; eelk&otilde;ige selleks, et mitte takistada asjaomaste toodete vedu, peavad k&otilde;nealused meetmed sisaldama ladustusaja pikendamisest tulenevaid kulutusi arvesse v&otilde;ttes kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud p&auml;evaraha maksmist ja asjakohase tagatise esitamise alusel s&otilde;lmitavaid kohapeal ladustamist k&auml;sitlevaid lepinguid ettev&otilde;tjatega, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud toodete valmistamist k&auml;sitlev leping; k&otilde;nealuste ettev&otilde;tjate n&otilde;usoleku puudumise korral tuleks s&auml;testada toodete &uuml;lev&otilde;tmine sekkumisametite poolt ja ladustamine nende vastutusel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the undertakings awarded contracts for the supply of canned beef should also qualify for the daily allowance to offset the extension of the period of storage where the dates for taking over the goods and making them available have been postponed owing to stock release difficulties at the German intervention agency in compliance with Article 12a of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1582/91 (5), as amended by Regulation (EEC) No 2546/91 (6); </inglise>
<eesti> ettev&otilde;tjatel, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud veiselihakonservide tarnimise lepingud, peaks samuti olema &otilde;igus saada p&auml;evaraha, et h&uuml;vitada ladustusaja pikenemist, kui kauba &uuml;lev&otilde;tmise ja k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise t&auml;htajad on l&uuml;katud edasi seoses raskustega v&auml;ljav&otilde;tmisel Saksa sekkumisameti laost vastavalt komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1582/91 (5) (muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2546/91) (6) artiklile 12a; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are to replace those adopted by abovementioned Regulation (EEC) No 2946/91; whereas the latter should accordingly be repealed; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed asendavad m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 2946/91 vastuv&otilde;etud meetmeid; k&otilde;nealune m&auml;&auml;rus tuleks seep&auml;rast kehtetuks tunnistada; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the exchange rate to be used to convert the daily allowance into the national currency should be specified and it should be fixed at a level reflecting the real economic situation; </inglise>
<eesti> p&auml;evarahade omav&auml;&auml;ringusse &uuml;mberarvestamisel kasutatav vahetuskurss tuleks m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks tasemel, mis peegeldab tegelikku majanduslikku olukorda; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Committee provided for in Article 5 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 598/91, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 598/91 artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Where products to be supplied under invitations to tender opened pursuant to Regulation (EEC) No 598/91 have not been taken over by the bodies designated by the Commission for their carriage to and distribution at the destination by the deadline for making them available, the intervention agencies in the Member States in which the products are stored shall ensure that the products are taken over under the terms laid down herein from the day following that deadline. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 598/91 kohaselt v&auml;ljakuulutatud pakkumismenetluste alusel tarnitavad tooteid ei ole komisjoni poolt k&otilde;nealuste toodete veoks ja sihtkohas jaotamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud asutused toodete k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise t&auml;htp&auml;evaks &uuml;le v&otilde;tnud, tagavad sekkumisametid liikmesriikides, kus tooteid ladustatakse, et tooted v&otilde;etakse &uuml;le k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud tingimustel alates k&otilde;nealusele t&auml;htp&auml;evale j&auml;rgnevast p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> The intervention agencies shall conclude storage contracts with the undertakings awarded contracts for the manufacture and packaging of the products who agree to keep the latter in storage until the date of actual take-over by the bodies responsible for transport or, where appropriate, until a decision is taken by the intervention agency after consulting the Commission to release those undertakings from their obligation to store the products. </inglise>
<eesti> Sekkumisametid s&otilde;lmivad ladustuslepingud nende ettev&otilde;tjatega, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud toodete valmistamist ja pakendamist k&auml;sitlevad lepingud ning kes on n&otilde;us ladustama tooteid kuni p&auml;evani, mil veo eest vastutav asutus need &uuml;le v&otilde;tab, v&otilde;i vajaduse korral kuni sekkumisamet teeb p&auml;rast komisjoniga konsulteerimist otsuse vabastada k&otilde;nealused ettev&otilde;tjad toodete ladustamise kohustusest. </eesti>
<inglise> Those contracts shall stipulate that the products are to be kept under suitable storage conditions against payment of a daily allowance of ECU 0,27 per tonne per day. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuses lepingus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks, et tooteid hoitakse sobivates ladustamistingimustes, saades p&auml;evaraha, mis on 0,27 ek&uuml;&uuml;d tonni kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> That amount shall be converted into national currency using the rate applicable on 16 October 1991 and published in the 'C' series of the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuse summa omav&auml;&auml;ringusse &uuml;mberarvestamisel kasutatakse 16. oktoobril 1991 kohaldatud ja Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teataja C-seerias avaldatud kurssi. </eesti>
<inglise> Such contracts shall entail an obligation to lodge a security in accordance with Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2220/85 (7), equal to the supply security provided for in the invitation to tender. </inglise>
<eesti> Sellised lepingud sisaldavad kohustust esitada vastavalt komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusele (EM&Uuml;) nr 2220/85 (7) pakkumismenetlusega etten&auml;htud tarnetagatisega v&otilde;rdne tagatis. </eesti>
<inglise> The primary requirement within the meaning of Article 20 of the abovementioned Regulation shall be storage of the product under suitable conditions until the end of the storage period as determined in Article 2. </inglise>
<eesti> Esman&otilde;ue eespool nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 20 m&auml;&auml;ratletud t&auml;henduses on toote ladustamine sobivates tingimustes kuni artiklis 2 kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud ladustusaja l&otilde;puni. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> Where the undertakings awarded contracts are unable to provide storage under the conditions laid down in Article 2, the intervention agencies shall take all measures necessary to take over the products themselves and store them until they are removed by the bodies responsible for carriage or, where applicable, until a decision is taken by the Commission regarding their disposal. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui ettev&otilde;tjad, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud lepingud, ei suuda tagada ladustamist artiklis 2 s&auml;testatud tingimustel, v&otilde;tavad sekkumisametid k&otilde;ik vajalikud meetmed, et v&otilde;tta tooted ise &uuml;le ja ladustada neid, kuni veo eest vastutav asutus need &auml;ra viib v&otilde;i vajaduse korral kuni komisjon teeb otsuse nende realiseerimise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> The costs arising from this operation shall be covered by standard allowances fixed pursuant to Article 6 (3) of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1883/78 of 2 August 1978 laying down general rules for the financing of interventions by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund, Guarantee Section (8). </inglise>
<eesti> K&otilde;nealuse toiminguga seotud kulud kaetakse n&otilde;ukogu 2. augusti 1978. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1883/78 (millega kehtestatakse &uuml;ldeeskirjad sekkumise finantseerimiseks Euroopa P&otilde;llumajanduse Arendus- ja Tagatisfondi tagatisrahastust) (8) artikli 6 l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud standardsummadega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Expenditure arising from such operations shall be entered in the accounts each month by the intervention agencies of the Member States and shall be shown in the accounts as expenditure on emergency aid to the Soviet Union. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikide sekkumisametid kannavad sellistest toimingutest tulenevad kulutused igal kuul raamatupidamisse N&otilde;ukogu Liidule antava h&auml;daabi kulutustena. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The following paragraph is hereby added to Article 12a of Regulation (EEC) No 1582/91: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1582/91 artiklile 12a lisatakse j&auml;rgmine l&otilde;ige: </eesti>
<inglise> '7. </inglise>
<eesti> "7. </eesti>
<inglise> The successful tenderers shall qualify on application for the daily allowance provided for in Article 2 of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3061/91 (*), from 23 October 1991 until the date of take-over by the body designated by the Commission if such take-over does not take place beforehand. </inglise>
<eesti> Edukatel pakkujatel on &otilde;igus saada taotluse korral komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3061/91* artikliga 2 etten&auml;htud p&auml;evaraha alates 23. oktoobrist 1991 kuni p&auml;evani, mil komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ratud asutus kauba &uuml;le v&otilde;tab, kui selline &uuml;lev&otilde;tmine ei toimu varem. </eesti>
<inglise> (*) OJ No L 289, 19.10.1991, p. 25. </inglise>
<eesti> * E&Uuml;T L 289, 19.10.1991, lk 25." </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 2946/91 is hereby repealed. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;rus (EM&Uuml;) nr 2946/91 tunnistatakse kehtetuks. </eesti>
 